{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1440,"text":"I'm an underwater explorer,"},{"time":5480,"text":"more specifically a cave diver."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9200,"text":"I wanted to be an astronaut\nwhen I was a little kid,"},{"time":11840,"text":"but growing up in Canada as a young girl,\nthat wasn't really available to me."},{"time":17680,"text":"But as it turns out,\nwe know a lot more about space"},{"time":21480,"text":"than we do about the underground waterways\ncoursing through our planet,"},{"time":25840,"text":"the very lifeblood of Mother Earth."},{"time":29720,"text":"So I decided to do something\nthat was even more remarkable."},{"time":33120,"text":"Instead of exploring outer space,"},{"time":35600,"text":"I wanted to explore\nthe wonders of inner space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39920,"text":"Now, a lot of people will tell you"},{"time":41600,"text":"that cave diving is perhaps\none of the most dangerous endeavors."},{"time":46560,"text":"I mean, imagine yourself\nhere in this room,"},{"time":49480,"text":"if you were suddenly\nplunged into blackness,"},{"time":52400,"text":"with your only job to find the exit,"},{"time":54840,"text":"sometimes swimming\nthrough these large spaces,"},{"time":57200,"text":"and at other times\ncrawling beneath the seats,"},{"time":60560,"text":"following a thin guideline,"},{"time":63120,"text":"just waiting for the life support\nto provide your very next breath."},{"time":67880,"text":"Well, that's my workplace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70760,"text":"But what I want to teach you today"},{"time":72760,"text":"is that our world\nis not one big solid rock."},{"time":77160,"text":"It's a whole lot more like a sponge."},{"time":79960,"text":"I can swim through a lot of the pores\nin our earth's sponge,"},{"time":83840,"text":"but where I can't,"},{"time":85280,"text":"other life-forms and other materials\ncan make that journey without me."},{"time":90320,"text":"And my voice is the one\nthat's going to teach you"},{"time":93360,"text":"about the inside of Mother Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98640,"text":"There was no guidebook available to me"},{"time":101640,"text":"when I decided to be the first person\nto cave dive inside Antarctic icebergs."},{"time":107720,"text":"In 2000, this was the largest\nmoving object on the planet."},{"time":112160,"text":"It calved off the Ross Ice Shelf,"},{"time":114200,"text":"and we went down there\nto explore ice edge ecology"},{"time":117160,"text":"and search for life-forms beneath the ice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120440,"text":"We use a technology called rebreathers."},{"time":123640,"text":"It's an awful lot like the same technology\nthat is used for space walks."},{"time":127880,"text":"This technology enables us to go deeper"},{"time":130360,"text":"than we could've imagined\neven 10 years ago."},{"time":133120,"text":"We use exotic gases,"},{"time":135200,"text":"and we can make missions\neven up to 20 hours long underwater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141160,"text":"I work with biologists."},{"time":143360,"text":"It turns out that caves\nare repositories of amazing life-forms,"},{"time":147920,"text":"species that we never knew existed before."},{"time":151760,"text":"Many of these life-forms\nlive in unusual ways."},{"time":155080,"text":"They have no pigment\nand no eyes in many cases,"},{"time":159040,"text":"and these animals\nare also extremely long-lived."},{"time":163560,"text":"In fact, animals swimming\nin these caves today"},{"time":167040,"text":"are identical in the fossil record"},{"time":169560,"text":"that predates the extinction\nof the dinosaurs."},{"time":172920,"text":"So imagine that: these are\nlike little swimming dinosaurs."},{"time":176680,"text":"What can they teach us\nabout evolution and survival?"},{"time":181120,"text":"When we look at an animal\nlike this remipede swimming in the jar,"},{"time":185160,"text":"he has giant fangs with venom."},{"time":188040,"text":"He can actually attack something\n40 times his size and kill it."},{"time":192320,"text":"If he were the size of a cat,"},{"time":194120,"text":"he'd be the most dangerous\nthing on our planet."},{"time":197920,"text":"And these animals live\nin remarkably beautiful places,"},{"time":201200,"text":"and in some cases,\ncaves like this, that are very young,"},{"time":205840,"text":"yet the animals are ancient."},{"time":207600,"text":"How did they get there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209880,"text":"I also work with physicists,"},{"time":212080,"text":"and they're interested oftentimes\nin global climate change."},{"time":215720,"text":"They can take rocks within the caves,"},{"time":218040,"text":"and they can slice them\nand look at the layers within with rocks,"},{"time":221120,"text":"much like the rings of a tree,"},{"time":223080,"text":"and they can count back in history"},{"time":225120,"text":"and learn about the climate on our planet\nat very different times."},{"time":228840,"text":"The red that you see in this photograph"},{"time":231360,"text":"is actually dust from the Sahara Desert."},{"time":234720,"text":"So it's been picked up by wind,\nblown across the Atlantic Ocean."},{"time":238840,"text":"It's rained down in this case\non the island of Abaco in the Bahamas."},{"time":243240,"text":"It soaks in through the ground"},{"time":244880,"text":"and deposits itself\nin the rocks within these caves."},{"time":248880,"text":"And when we look back in the layers\nof these rocks, we can find times"},{"time":252720,"text":"when the climate\nwas very, very dry on earth,"},{"time":255520,"text":"and we can go back\nmany hundreds of thousands of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260560,"text":"Paleoclimatologists are also interested"},{"time":262840,"text":"in where the sea level stands were\nat other times on earth."},{"time":266160,"text":"Here in Bermuda, my team and I embarked"},{"time":268400,"text":"on the deepest manned dives\never conducted in the region,"},{"time":271480,"text":"and we were looking for places"},{"time":273120,"text":"where the sea level\nused to lap up against the shoreline,"},{"time":276680,"text":"many hundreds of feet\nbelow current levels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280880,"text":"I also get to work with paleontologists\nand archaeologists."},{"time":284400,"text":"In places like Mexico,\nin the Bahamas, and even in Cuba,"},{"time":288800,"text":"we're looking at cultural remains\nand also human remains in caves,"},{"time":293520,"text":"and they tell us a lot"},{"time":294800,"text":"about some of the earliest\ninhabitants of these regions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298760,"text":"But my very favorite project of all\nwas over 15 years ago,"},{"time":302280,"text":"when I was a part of the team\nthat made the very first"},{"time":304828,"text":"accurate, three-dimensional map\nof a subterranean surface."},{"time":308160,"text":"This device that I'm\ndriving through the cave"},{"time":310560,"text":"was actually creating\na three-dimensional model as we drove it."},{"time":315040,"text":"We also used ultra low frequency radio"},{"time":317120,"text":"to broadcast back to the surface\nour exact position within the cave."},{"time":322320,"text":"So I swam under houses and businesses\nand bowling alleys and golf courses,"},{"time":327160,"text":"and even under a Sonny's BBQ Restaurant,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":331080,"text":"Pretty remarkable, and what that taught me"},{"time":333200,"text":"was that everything we do\non the surface of our earth"},{"time":336120,"text":"will be returned to us to drink."},{"time":338560,"text":"Our water planet is not just\nrivers, lakes and oceans,"},{"time":343360,"text":"but it's this vast network of groundwater\nthat knits us all together."},{"time":348160,"text":"It's a shared resource\nfrom which we all drink."},{"time":352040,"text":"And when we can understand\nour human connections with our groundwater"},{"time":356360,"text":"and all of our water resources\non this planet,"},{"time":359040,"text":"then we'll be working on the problem"},{"time":360800,"text":"that's probably the most important\nissue of this century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365040,"text":"So I never got to be that astronaut\nthat I always wanted to be,"},{"time":368480,"text":"but this mapping device,\ndesigned by Dr. Bill Stone, will be."},{"time":372120,"text":"It's actually morphed."},{"time":373560,"text":"It's now a self-swimming autonomous robot,"},{"time":376880,"text":"artificially intelligent,"},{"time":378560,"text":"and its ultimate goal\nis to go to Jupiter's moon Europa"},{"time":382160,"text":"and explore oceans beneath\nthe frozen surface of that body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387480,"text":"And that's pretty amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390160,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}